18
00:00:32,840 --> 00:00:36,920
experience. For example, take a look at

19
00:00:34,920 --> 00:00:38,960
this table. It seems relatively

20
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:41,080
logically laid out, but clearly nothing

21
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:42,720
is driving the form. But, for example,

22
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:44,920
if we turned the department and

23
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:46,800
employment into chips or took these

24
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:48,600
numbers and right align them, things

25
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:50,800
start to shape up. We do this because

26
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:52,720
there's only a set number of departments

27
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:55,280
or employment statuses, and we right

28
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:57,240
align the numbers so the digits align by

29
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:59,400
place value. Then, we can augment this

30
00:00:57,240 --> 00:01:01,200
further by truncating long text to give

31
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:03,480
