32
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:06,240
or even shade out rows of the table that

33
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:08,360
are inactive or deactivated. And when we

34
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:10,400
compare the before and after, we can

35
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:12,080
clearly see which is more visually

36
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:14,120
appealing to look at and importantly,

37
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:16,560
which is letting the data drive the

38
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:18,360
form. And the same is true for data that

39
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:20,240
probably shouldn't even be in a table in

40
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:22,320
the first place. This table definitely

