00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:30,880
aren't letting the data determine the

45
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:32,640
shape of the UI. Instead, if we were to

46
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:34,720
arrange this as a timeline, it starts to

47
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:36,800
become a lot easier to follow rather

48
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:38,280
than a time sorted table. This form

49
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:40,320
factor could then be tucked into a

50
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:42,400
sidebar pop out or made wider as a

51
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:44,520
second column beside the table, but

52
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:47,240
either way, now we're letting the data

53
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:49,320
drive the UI. And color is a very

54
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:50,600
important consideration when we do start

55
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:52,000
designing these tables. [music]

56
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:54,600
Landing pages, you can get away with a

57
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:56,560
lot, but dashboard colors shouldn't just

58
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:58,640
be sprinkled in to look nice. It should

59
00:01:56,560 --> 00:02:01,040
come from the data itself. In these

60
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:03,000
