72
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:25,640
our previous example.

73
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:30,240
Often when I talk about hierarchy, I use

74
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:32,480
examples like this, where this card has

75
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:34,520
poor hierarchy, and this card has strong

76
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:36,680
hierarchy. But there's another type of

77
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:38,120
hierarchy based on what you show and

78
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:40,400
what you hide, and it's called

79
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:42,120
progressive disclosure. For example,

80
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:44,160
this share functionality isn't

81
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:45,959
permanently ingrained in the side of the

82
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:48,040
table since it's not that frequently

83
00:02:45,959 --> 00:02:49,840
accessed and frankly not important

84
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:51,880
enough. Instead, we tuck it into a

85
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:53,880
popover so we don't have to rip the user

86
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:55,959
to an entirely different page. And

87
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:57,640
within this popover, the primary action

88
00:02:55,959 --> 00:02:59,880
is of course the search box, which is

89
00:02:57,640 --> 00:03:02,800
why it's immediately visible at the top.

90
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:04,720
A secondary action like removing a user

91
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:06,760
isn't overly important, so instead of

92
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:08,600
ingraining it in the UI, we show the

93
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:10,880
remove button on hover along with a

94
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:13,120
tooltip. We could be more explicit by

95
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:15,040
always having them, or even still more

96
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:17,200
explicit by having the full label

97
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:19,440
present. But since we're tight on space

98
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:22,280
and removing a user from sharing isn't a

99
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:24,200
main action, we progressively reveal it

100
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:26,120
as soon as the user starts to look for

101
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:28,080
that functionality. And what I've just

102
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:30,640
described is called the spectrum of

103
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:32,600
explicitness, where a global, always

104
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:35,280
visible share button is quite high,

105
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:38,200
whereas an icon to copy a cell on hover

106
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:40,000
is much lower on that same spectrum. And

107
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:42,320
Apple does the same thing really well in

108
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:44,720
their Reminders app. On swipe left and

109
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:46,760
right, it reveals useful but secondary

110
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:48,800
actions compared to actually checking

111
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:50,840
